HEADWORD: Penciling
<hw>Pen"cil*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>pencilling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The work of the pencil or
brush; <as>as, delicate <ex>penciling</ex> in a picture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Brickwork)</fld> <def>Lines of white or black paint
drawn along a mortar joint in a brick wall.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pencillated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Pencillate</ent>⟦br⟧
